message: Would you mind if I ask what you’re looking for on tinder? What do you hope to find?
I didn’t expect to have this conversation.
To answer your second question: I’m not sure. I dislike when my secrets are repeated and I think over time that has led me to confide in less people with large overlapping social circles.

My childhood was good for the most part. I went to a very small school and didn’t have many friends there but overall there was little trauma. I shouldn’t say that I’m broken, rather I should say that I tend to optimize my life in ways that may be considered abnormal. I am passively searching for purpose and meaning, which can lead to being discontent.
Also is there something about you that prevents people from confiding in you? I guess now we’re going into the psyche, but you brought it there.
*know

Do you think you’re broken? Childhood trauma? I never insinuated you were broken, but more just wanted to your social skill level because engineers tend to be limited in that sphere. I don’t think social skills necessarily correlate to being broken. And I always skip pleasantries or just dodge them if someone tries to initiate them.

Sometimes? I know a lot of people but am vulnerable to very few. I think most of the people I surround myself with are deeply unhappy or feel broken in irreparable ways, and sometimes we bond over that. I think a lot of people have unhappy but unwilling to express their own unhappiness around me, which creates an untenable situation.

I enjoy that you skipped pleasantries and meaningless banter and moved directly into the “in what ways are you broken?” conversation, even if it was initiated and guided by me. Very few of my conversations start with “‘nice smile” or “you’re cute” so perhaps this is more representative of my norm.
*psychiatrists

Got you. Well, a 4 or a 5 seems approachable. Do you get along/understand people who are more in the 7-8 range? I offend people too and am often judged as an unapproachable asshole, but I’m also conscious of that...most of the time. You mean most of the psychiatrist you’ve seen. And yeah, I’m neurotic, but not bizarre like some psychiatrists I’ve met. Is it not representative of your tinder conversations? I don’t know if I have a typical tinder conversation standard, especially since so many start with “you’re cute” or “nice smile” and then they have to end.

Probably around a 4 or 5. A lot of my responses are fairly robotic. I’m better now than when I was little. I actively try to build reminders to be conscious and cognizant into my life. Im very good at remembering specific details but bad at reading emotions and I often offend people without meaning to. I have a very dry, sarcastic, and often self deprecating sense of humor that helps mask some of these traits. Some people think that I’m a provocateur / “a dick” instead of having low social development. 

I have anecdotal evidence to support your claim. Most of the psychiatrists I know have weird personality quirks. 

What did you do in tech? Is our dialogue representative of your typical tinder conversation?

But if you’re self-aware enough to know they’re terrible, they can’t be that terrible. I used to work in tech, and if you think of the most Aspergers engineer as a 1 and the most gregarious/intuitive person as a 10, where are you? Mine are decent — I’m perceptive and easy-going, but not the most gregarious in a group setting. Psychiatry is actually known for attracting people with bad social skills because they all have psychological problems or are just very eccentric.
How are your social skills? Probably less terrible?
My parents put a computer in my bedroom in 1993. They doomed me early on.
I admire your career aspirations. My social skills terrible! One of my interns claims that I’m actively making her more awkward.

No one knows what it is and it’s actually only existed for a few years anyways. I’m aiming to work in inpatient psych in a hospital, ideally forensic, but that might shift. I won’t diagnose you with anything, although as a coder, how are your social skills?

I honestly think it’s better to be unsuccessful than to be stuck in a median between success and failure. Of course I know what a DNP is! Still, I’m terrified that you will diagnose me with something serious. What do you plan on doing after school?

You describe your job so enthusiastically. At least, you’re unsuccessful. So you know what a DNP is. Yes, I’m in the psych DNP program and am a year and a half in. Also, don’t worry about being analyzed. I’m usually open-minded in my character assessments of people I meet.

I don't think we should ever meet. I'm terrified that you'll diagnose some previously unidentified mental illness that I most likely have. I am an engineer at my own unsuccessful, small, boutique hedge fund. My job title is Software Engineer but in reality, I mostly create powerpoint slides for attorneys and slowly poison the minds of everyone around me.  How far along are you in your program? Are you a DNP student?
Where are you an engineer?
I guess it was the Yale club, but it was a party for a yacht club. Didn’t go to the roof. I’m in nurse practitioner school if you know what that is. For psychiatry.
What do you study?
I’m a terrible sailor and have only nearly died twice. He Yale yacht club or the Yale club? The best part about the Yale club is the library. The second best part is the rooftop.

You have to be a decent sailor to navigate this part of the Hudson. Not sure if that’s true or not, but that’s what my dad tells me. I’ve spent some time at the Yale yacht club in NY and was thoroughly miserable. Spent about 40 minutes sitting in their library avoiding the scene.

Oxford commas are the best. By my elderly cat, I mean cat that lives upstate with my parents. So, my bathroom smells minimally of cat shit. I keep my sailboat at pier 40 off W. Houston. It’s moored, so there’s no yacht club.

Apparently, you also appreciate the Oxford comma. I can accept an elderly cat and a shitty sail boat...Where do you store that boat in New York? And how intensely does your bathroom smell like cat shit?
And by kittens, I mean elderly cat, and by yacht, I mean small shitty sailboat.
Is it still baiting if I alert you ahead of time about attempting to swoon you with kittens and my yacht?
